'''Shiratori Kofun''' (白鳥古墳, Shiratori Kofun) is the name of several Kofuns (kofun) in Japan.
* {{ill|Shiratori Kofun Group|ja|白鳥古墳群|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiratori Kofun Group}} - Located in {{ill|Moriyama Ward, Nagoya|ja|守山区|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriyama Ward, Nagoya|qq=}}, Nagoya, Aichi Prefecture. Pronounced ''Shiratori Kofun-gun.'' * {{ill|Shiratori Kofun (Nagoya)|ja|白鳥古墳 (名古屋市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiratori Kofun (Nagoya)|qq=}} - Located in {{ill|Atsuta Ward, Nagoya|ja|熱田区|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Atsuta Ward, Nagoya|qq=}}, Nagoya, Aichi Prefecture. Pronounced ''Shirotori Kofun.'' * {{ill|Shiratori Kofun (Higashihiroshima)|ja|白鳥古墳 (東広島市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiratori Kofun (Higashihiroshima)|qq=}} - Located in {{ill|Higashihiroshima|ja|東広島市|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Higashihiroshima|qq=}}, Hiroshima Prefecture. Pronounced ''Shiratori Kofun.'' * {{ill|Shiratori Kofun (Hirao)|ja|白鳥古墳 (平生町)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiratori Kofun (Hirao)|qq=}} - Located in {{ill|Hirao|ja|平生町|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirao|qq=}}, Kumage District, Yamaguchi Prefecture. Pronounced ''Shiratori Kofun.''
